==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sluiceway
<hw>Sluice"way`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An artificial
channel into which water is let by a sluice; specifically, a trough
constructed over the bed of a stream, so that logs, lumber, or rubbish
can be floated down to some convenient place of delivery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sluicy</ent>⟦br⟧
